cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.DB

This paper involves machine learning models for predicting disease onset using longitudinal lab test data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves healthcare applications, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a likely second choice. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as additional likely categories. Finally, the use of administrative claims data suggests the category cs.DB (Databases) as a possible fifth choice.
